description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a part time Band 3 to work in the Trauma and Orthopaedic Physiotherapy service. We are looking for a new team member with excellent communication and motivational skills to join our busy T&amp;O department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, friendly, reliable and hardworking individual who is passionate about patient care, who can work both independently and function well in a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this ward based role you will primarily work under the indirect supervision of Physiotherapists; you must be able to work well both individually and as part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role you can look forward to a career full of development opportunities and the support from an excellent team of Chartered Physiotherapists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 08/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Leanne O&#39;Brien&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Clinical Specalist Physiotherapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Leanne.O&#39;Brien@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01685 721721 bleep 324&lt;/p&gt;
